Pre-Game Insights: Ireland manager Heimir Hallgrímsson and captain Nathan Collins are beginning their international partnership with this match.
Ireland is experiencing one of the grimmest periods in its football history, with a downward spiral of results.
Ireland has lost eight of their last 10 competitive matches, with no goals scored and seven conceded in the last three.
Nathan Collins expressed frustration with the team's recent performance and emphasized the desire to win and qualify for tournaments.
Ireland's squad is valued significantly higher than Finland's, but Finland's experience and home advantage could be decisive.
Finland manager Markku Kanerva will be without injured midfielder Kaan Kairinen, but captain Lucas Hradecky will lead the team.
Teemu Pukki, despite a hamstring issue, is a key player for Finland with 42 goals from 123 caps.
Hallgrímsson acknowledged the tactical and hard-working nature of the Finnish team.
